# Security — <%= appName %>

Fastify security plugins: Helmet headers, CORS, and rate limiting.

## Environment

```env
CORS_ORIGIN=http://localhost:3000
RATE_LIMIT_MAX=100
RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW=1 minute
```

## Usage

```typescript
import { registerSecurityPlugins } from './src/platform/security/index.js';

await registerSecurityPlugins(app);
```

Run `my security setup` to regenerate this module.

## Dependency audit

```bash
my security audit
my doctor                 # includes npm/pnpm audit unless --skip-audit
```

## Secret scanning

```bash
my security scan-secrets
```

Uses lightweight regex heuristics (AWS keys, private keys, JWT-like strings). For CI, consider [TruffleHog](https://github.com/trufflesecurity/trufflehog) or [Gitleaks](https://github.com/gitleaks/gitleaks).

## CI scanning (Snyk / Trivy)

Add to your pipeline after build:

```yaml
# Snyk (example)
- run: npx snyk test --severity-threshold=high

# Trivy filesystem scan (example)
- run: trivy fs --scanners vuln,secret .
```

See generated GitHub/GitLab CI workflows under `.github/workflows/` or `.gitlab-ci.yml` for lint/test stages you can extend.
